Wash and separate the leaves from iceberg lettuce. Whisk hoisin, garlic, ginger, chili paste and lime juice in a small bowl. Heat oil in large saut pan over medium-high heat. Brown ground beef. Season with salt and pepper, add peppers and cook for 2-3 minutes. Add the hoisin sauce mixture and stir for 2-3 minutes. To serve: Scoop a little of the beef mixture into a lettuce leaf. Top with a few chow mein noodles and roll to eat with hands.